</div>
<p><span class="text-grey">Research areas: </span>neuro-symbolic AI, foundation models, logical rule induction, inductive logic programming (ILP), deep learning, explainable AI (XAI), time series analysis, and robustness.</p>
<p class="text-grey">Have interesting projects or want to have some discussion? You can contact me at <span class="text-dark email-nowrap">phua<span class="replace"> [at] </span>comp.isct.ac.jp</span></p>
<h2>Goal</h2>
<p class="text-grey">Neural networks now drive most of AI, but the knowledge they acquire remains impenetrable to the people who rely on them. My long-term goal is to make that knowledge <strong class="text-dark">readable</strong>, <strong class="text-dark">auditable</strong>, and <strong class="text-dark">correctable</strong> — so that a doctor, an engineer, or a scientist can see what a model has learned, challenge it, and build on it. Toward this, I am developing foundation models that learn generalizable, interpretable knowledge from background knowledge and limited data, and logical reasoning techniques that make generative AI reliable.</p>
